---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About StackSwitch — Independent SaaS Comparisons"
  description="Learn how StackSwitch compares SaaS tools. Our methodology uses publicly available pricing, official docs, and verified user reviews — no vendor bias."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About StackSwitch</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-10">
      Independent software comparisons built for buyers, not vendors.
    </p>

    <!-- Trust shield SVG -->
    <div class="flex justify-center mb-12">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 200 200" class="w-40 h-40" aria-hidden="true">
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="shield-grad" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#6366f1" stop-opacity="0.12"/>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#6366f1" stop-opacity="0.03"/>
          </linearGradient>
        </defs>
        <!-- Shield shape -->
        <path d="M100 16 L168 48 L168 108 Q168 156 100 184 Q32 156 32 108 L32 48 Z"
              fill="url(#shield-grad)" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="2"/>
        <!-- Checkmark -->
        <path d="M72 100 L92 120 L128 76" fill="none" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        <!-- Small accent lines -->
        <line x1="60" y1="52" x2="140" y2="52" stroke="#c7d2fe" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5"/>
        <line x1="56" y1="62" x2="144" y2="62" stroke="#c7d2fe" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- Mission -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Our mission</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        StackSwitch exists to help teams make better software decisions without vendor bias. Choosing the right SaaS tool
        can save thousands of pounds a year and hundreds of hours in productivity — but most comparison sites are funded
        by the tools they review, which skews the recommendations.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        We built StackSwitch to be the comparison resource we wished existed: clear data, honest trade-offs, and no hidden
        incentives pushing you towards a particular product.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- How we compare tools -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How we compare tools</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Every comparison on StackSwitch follows a consistent, repeatable methodology. Here is how we do it:
      </p>

      <!-- Methodology SVG: 3-step process -->
      <div class="flex justify-center mb-8">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 600 140" class="w-full max-w-xl" aria-hidden="true">
          <!-- Step 1: Research -->
          <rect x="16" y="20" width="160" height="100" rx="12" fill="white" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="52" cy="52" r="16" fill="#6366f1" opacity="0.1"/>
          <text x="52" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" font-weight="700" fill="#6366f1" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">1</text>
          <text x="80" y="56" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#1f2937" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Research</text>
          <text x="32" y="80" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Pricing from official sites</text>
          <text x="32" y="94" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Features from docs</text>
          <text x="32" y="108" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Ratings from G2/Capterra</text>

          <!-- Arrow 1 -->
          <line x1="186" y1="70" x2="216" y2="70" stroke="#c7d2fe" stroke-width="2"/>
          <polygon points="216,64 228,70 216,76" fill="#c7d2fe"/>

          <!-- Step 2: Compare -->
          <rect x="232" y="20" width="160" height="100" rx="12" fill="white" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="268" cy="52" r="16" fill="#6366f1" opacity="0.1"/>
          <text x="268" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" font-weight="700" fill="#6366f1" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">2</text>
          <text x="296" y="56" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#1f2937" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Compare</text>
          <text x="248" y="80" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Side-by-side pricing</text>
          <text x="248" y="94" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Feature matching</text>
          <text x="248" y="108" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Pros and cons analysis</text>

          <!-- Arrow 2 -->
          <line x1="402" y1="70" x2="432" y2="70" stroke="#c7d2fe" stroke-width="2"/>
          <polygon points="432,64 444,70 432,76" fill="#c7d2fe"/>

          <!-- Step 3: Recommend -->
          <rect x="448" y="20" width="140" height="100" rx="12" fill="white" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="484" cy="52" r="16" fill="#6366f1" opacity="0.1"/>
          <text x="484" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" font-weight="700" fill="#6366f1" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">3</text>
          <text x="508" y="56" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="#1f2937" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Recommend</text>
          <text x="464" y="80" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Verdicts by use case</text>
          <text x="464" y="94" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Budget-based picks</text>
          <text x="464" y="108" font-size="9" fill="#6b7280" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">Clear trade-offs</text>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <strong>Data collection:</strong> We gather pricing information directly from official product websites and documentation.
          Feature lists come from vendor docs, changelogs, and help centres. User sentiment is sourced from verified reviews on
          G2 and Capterra — platforms where reviewers must prove they use the software.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Structured comparison:</strong> Each tool is evaluated on the same criteria: starting price, pricing model,
          free plan availability, core features, G2 score, and Capterra score. This makes apples-to-apples comparison possible
          across categories.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Context-aware verdicts:</strong> Rather than declaring a single "winner", we explain which tool suits
          which use case. The best CRM for a 5-person startup is rarely the best for a 500-person enterprise.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Editorial independence -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Editorial independence</h2>
      <div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-indigo-600 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <span><strong>No sponsored placements.</strong> Tool rankings are based on user ratings and feature fit — not payments from vendors.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-indigo-600 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <span><strong>No affiliate links influencing rankings.</strong> Where we include affiliate links, they never affect which tool is ranked first or recommended.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-indigo-600 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <span><strong>Transparent data sources.</strong> Every data point we cite — pricing, ratings, features — can be verified on the original source.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-indigo-600 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <span><strong>Regular updates.</strong> Pricing changes frequently in SaaS. We review and update our data to keep comparisons accurate.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Have a question about our methodology, or spotted something that needs updating?
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-indigo-600 text-white px-6 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-colors">
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
